
           Instructions for FIXPALET.GFA OR FIXPALET.PRG

     Fixpalet will set your desktop colors the way you want them 
without having to keep the control panel in memory, saving some RAM
for more important uses.
     To set the colors you wish to use, power-up your ST with the 
control panel installed, and set the color values in the normal way.
When you are satisfied, exit the control panel and choose "Save Desktop"
from the menu bar. The desired color values are then stored in the 
"Desktop.inf" file on your boot disk.(Or on c:\ for hard disk users)
     Now you can run fixpalet.prg and it will load the colors chosen
from the control panel, and creat a file called palette.dat which it
will use from then on, instead of reading the desktop.inf file.
     Unfortunately, this program is of no use in an AUTO folder. The 
reason for this is that the GEM system variables and desktop conf-
iguration are not loaded from ROM until all AUTO programs are run. 
Even though Fixpalet works in an AUTO folder, the default colors are
loaded right before the desktop comes up. Because of this, you must run 
Fixpalet from the desktop(or through the GFA interpreter), until GFA is
modified to allow the creation of desk accessories.
     For hackers, the source code might seem a little odd, but it was 
necessary to convert the numbers as found in the desktop.inf from three
bytes per color to one word(2 bytes) per color.  Example:

          DESKTOP FORMAT                PALETTE.DAT
          white= 7,7,7 (3 bytes)        white= 1911 (2 bytes)


